ODE H.

Caius Crispus Sallust, to whom this ode is addressed, was the son of the sister of the distinguished historian of the same name. He was a gentleman of equestrian rank and splendid fortune. He stood high at court, being a particular favorite of Augustus. But he was rational in his views of happiness, and wished to increase neither his rank nor his fortune.
